    <h1>My 3rd Year Coding Showcase</h1>
	
	<h2>Individual HTML Project - My Football Website</h2>
	
	<p>In third year, we began learning HTML. This allowed us to code and create websites. I worked by myself for this project, so I decided to do my project on something I had an interest in: football. 

	<br><br>I used the website Thimble to create my website, as it split the screen so you had a live update of what your code would make a webpage look like. On my website, I stretched my coding abilities by using a vast range of code, such as <b>tables, marquee, div, class, id, linear gradient, float</b> and I learned how to change the colour of links. I used a table to list the 5 biggest leagues in the world, what countries they are hosted in and who are the current title holders of each league. I fully customised and edited the table so that each block was the home colours of the title holder of that league. I made the title of the website move in a rotation using <b>marquee</b>. I used <b>div</b> to group paragraphs of information together so it was easier to style all of them. I used external links which led you to the current league table of that league, and I used internal links to make it easier to navigate the page. Here is a link to my website on Thimble:
</p>
	<br><a href="https://thimble.mozilla.org/en-US/user/soggy-biscuit123/1896940/">My Football Website on Thimble</a>
	
